WEBVTT

00:00.574 --> 00:02.158
Hi. My name is Bridgette Dubois,

00:03.024 --> 00:05.659
and I'm going into seventh grade
at Bates Middle School.

00:05.710 --> 00:09.580
I'm taking a media class,
and my summer homework

00:09.664 --> 00:12.866
was to create a movie
about someone I met

00:12.918 --> 00:15.920
or an experience I had
this summer.

00:16.004 --> 00:18.656
This is my video.

00:26.881 --> 00:31.335
<i>Before you meet our houseguest,</i>
<i>I want you to meet my family.</i>

00:31.403 --> 00:33.003
Go away.

00:33.071 --> 00:34.738
<i>This is my little sister,</i>
<i>Marie.</i>

00:34.806 --> 00:37.074
<i>Or at least that's her eye.</i>

00:37.142 --> 00:38.692
<i>I know you're probably</i>
<i>wondering</i>

00:38.743 --> 00:40.444
<i>what the rest of her is like,</i>

00:40.528 --> 00:43.497
<i>but it's okay--</i>
<i>you're not missing anything.</i>

00:44.783 --> 00:47.184
Bridgette, turn that camera off!

00:47.252 --> 00:48.986
<i>This is my older sister, Ariel.</i>

00:49.054 --> 00:51.155
<i>She thinks she's God</i>
<i>'cause she can drive</i>

00:51.222 --> 00:54.041
<i>and is kind of pretty</i>
<i>and got born before I did.</i>

00:54.092 --> 00:55.592
<i>But I don't care.</i>

00:55.677 --> 00:58.212
<i>She's leaving for college soon,</i>
<i>and then I'll be God...</i>

00:58.263 --> 00:59.930
<i>if you don't count Mom and Dad.</i>

01:00.015 --> 01:01.298
Put that thing away!

01:04.468 --> 01:05.769
<i>This is my dad.</i>

01:05.837 --> 01:08.472
<i>He falls asleep on the couch</i>
<i>a lot on weekends.</i>

01:08.540 --> 01:10.808
<i>My mom keeps saying</i>
<i>not to wake him up.</i>

01:10.875 --> 01:13.610
<i>It's not</i> his <i>fault</i>
<i>that he's so sleepy.</i>

01:13.695 --> 01:17.348
<i>I don't get it, but that's</i>
<i>adult stuff, and it bores me.</i>

01:18.800 --> 01:20.334
<i>And this is my mom.</i>

01:20.402 --> 01:23.787
<i>She has a really cool job at</i>
<i>the district attorney's office.</i>

01:23.872 --> 01:26.240
Look, I'm sorry.
I can't help you.

01:26.291 --> 01:29.626
And I'd really appreciate it
if you'd just leave my house.

01:29.711 --> 01:30.878
Leave your house?

01:30.945 --> 01:33.380
What kind of respect
for the dead is that?

01:33.448 --> 01:35.916
Bad enough I can't
taste nothing.

01:35.967 --> 01:38.969
Bad enough I can't change
out of this suit.

01:39.054 --> 01:40.554
Bad enough I can't do nothing

01:40.621 --> 01:43.123
about this unfortunate blemish
I got here.

01:43.174 --> 01:45.793
And now I got to deal
with your bad attitude?

01:45.860 --> 01:47.628
<i>And this</i>
<i>is our summer houseguest.</i>

01:47.696 --> 01:49.029
<i>His name is Tony.</i>

01:49.097 --> 01:51.031
<i>And, oh, yeah... he's dead.</i>

01:51.099 --> 01:53.567
<i>You see, my mom talks</i>
<i>to dead people,</i>

01:53.634 --> 01:55.736
<i>and sometimes they drop by</i>
<i>to ask her things,</i>

01:55.803 --> 01:57.771
<i>whether they're invited or not.</i>

01:57.822 --> 01:59.639
Have a little pity,
psychic lady.

01:59.691 --> 02:01.141
How would you like it?

02:01.192 --> 02:03.160
You're walking down the street
minding your own business

02:03.278 --> 02:05.162
and a bunch of goons
sneak up behind you,

02:05.246 --> 02:06.480
put a bag on
your head,

02:06.531 --> 02:08.582
throw you in the trunk
of a car, and pop-pop,

02:08.649 --> 02:10.484
next thing you know, you're
buried under an overpass,

02:10.535 --> 02:11.919
never to be heard
from again.

02:11.986 --> 02:13.754
Leave me alone.

02:13.821 --> 02:15.489
You talking to me?

02:15.540 --> 02:16.874
No!
No.

02:17.876 --> 02:19.426
I just want names.

02:19.494 --> 02:21.128
Tell me who did this to me.

02:21.179 --> 02:22.379
I know you can do it.

02:22.464 --> 02:25.049
I heard about you
from well-connected people.

02:25.133 --> 02:27.000
No. I'm sorry.
I can't help you.

02:27.052 --> 02:29.436
I just don't
help bad men.

02:29.504 --> 02:30.771
Wait a second.

02:30.838 --> 02:33.357
What makes you think
I'm a bad man?

02:33.441 --> 02:36.443
You can tell
by just looking at me?

02:36.511 --> 02:39.480
<i>Tony decided he was going</i>
<i>to wear Mom down.</i>

02:39.531 --> 02:41.231
<i>He'd stay as long as it took.</i>

02:41.316 --> 02:42.866
Classic, shmassic.

02:42.951 --> 02:44.535
This movie's ridiculous.

02:44.619 --> 02:46.537
Shh.

02:46.621 --> 02:50.791
I don't even think
Jimmy Caan is Italian.

02:50.858 --> 02:53.660
Is he still here?

02:53.711 --> 02:56.330
<i>My dad had the hardest time</i>
<i>with it.</i>

02:56.381 --> 02:59.750
<i>The rest of us</i>
<i>thought he was fun.</i>

02:59.834 --> 03:03.170
And if you roll two sixes,
what do you call that?

03:03.221 --> 03:04.555
Boxcars!

03:04.639 --> 03:07.241
Right again, sweetheart.

03:07.308 --> 03:09.393
<i>But the nights</i>
<i>were hard for him.</i>

03:09.461 --> 03:11.445
<i>Ghosts don't sleep, you know.</i>

03:11.513 --> 03:13.931
Come on. What do you say
we put on a little music,

03:14.015 --> 03:16.567
have a little fun?

03:23.108 --> 03:24.508
Anyone got the password

03:24.576 --> 03:27.611
so I can get the adult channel
on the cable?

03:32.250 --> 03:34.001
I don't think your
mother's ever

03:34.068 --> 03:36.587
going to tell me
what I need to know.

03:36.671 --> 03:40.374
She's afraid you'll find a way
to get even somehow.

03:40.425 --> 03:44.094
She doesn't want to be
a part of anyone getting hurt.

03:45.630 --> 03:48.632
I think I got to get out
of here, Bridgette.

03:48.716 --> 03:51.185
There's some place
I'm supposed to be,

03:51.252 --> 03:54.054
and I think it's time
I get there.

03:54.122 --> 03:56.473
I'm going
to miss you, Tony.

03:56.558 --> 03:58.892
I think you're
the coolest.

03:58.943 --> 04:00.444
You know what?

04:00.528 --> 04:03.197
I am the coolest.

04:03.264 --> 04:05.265
You wouldn't happen to know
where your father keeps

04:05.316 --> 04:08.001
his ATM card, would you?

04:08.069 --> 04:12.673
<i>And then, one day, we woke up,</i>
<i>and he was just gone.</i>

04:12.740 --> 04:15.942
<i>Just disappeared.</i>

04:18.129 --> 04:19.997
I still miss him.

04:20.081 --> 04:21.714
I thought that he was

04:21.781 --> 04:24.418
the most amazing human being
I'd ever met.

04:24.469 --> 04:27.304
And maybe that's why
I've decided that,

04:27.388 --> 04:29.923
instead of starting
seventh grade today,

04:29.974 --> 04:33.227
I'm going to embark
on a life of crime.

04:33.294 --> 04:35.979
Oh, which reminds me...

04:37.682 --> 04:41.018
Mom, I've got your car keys,
and I've got your wallet.

04:41.102 --> 04:42.469
And don't worry.

04:42.520 --> 04:45.072
Once I make it
over the state line, I'll call.

04:52.647 --> 04:54.698
You okay?

04:54.782 --> 04:55.782
Yeah. No.

04:55.833 --> 04:57.651
Just a weird,
stupid dream.

04:57.702 --> 05:00.854
Bridgette, first day
of middle school.

05:00.922 --> 05:02.489
Just makes me nervous.

05:02.557 --> 05:04.358
Relax. It's going
to be fine.

05:04.425 --> 05:06.293
It's school.

05:06.344 --> 05:09.996
It's not like she's going to
be hanging out with criminals.

05:16.054 --> 05:17.221
Where are you going?

05:17.305 --> 05:18.972
It's still early.

05:19.023 --> 05:22.209
I got to find my car keys
and my wallet.

